Doc.1 --> To integrate image in any questions

<div class="image">
    <img src="" alt="">
</div>

The above code with the image src should be put just after the closing tag of para tag i.e; </p> with class="qno" As in
the example below
<!-- Question-no2 -->
<div id="questions" class="mt-30 mb-40 flex-row">
    <div class="qns-no">
        <p>2. </p>
    </div>
    <div class="question">
        <p class="qno">This are contains the Question
        </p>
        <div class="image">
            <img src="/pictures/CSIT/1 sem Digital Logic/2075-Qno-2.png" alt="">
        </div>
    </div>
</div>



Doc.2 ---> Integrate any math equations in the webpage

MathJax is used for inserting beautiful mathematical equations in the webpages with the following line of code in HTML

<script src="https://polyfill.io/v3/polyfill.min.js?features=es6"></script>
<script type="text/javascript" id="MathJax-script" async src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mathjax@3/es5/tex-chtml.js">
</script>

Doc.3 ---> Writing the equations

First of all the math equations are converted into the Tex or LaTex format currently
(https://www.codecogs.com/eqnedit.php) site
is used to convert the mathematical equation into LaTex format.
After the conversion the LaTex form of the mathematical equation should is to be inserted inside the tag below (between
the $$ .. $$signs)
<p class="mathjax">$$ $$</p>
---> the latex form of equation should be inserted between the $$ $$ signs